<h3 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"><big style="text-decoration: underline;"><big><img style="width: 129px; height: 114px;" alt="" src="images-2.jpeg" align="left">Pizza Order Form
Lesson</big></big></h3>

<div style="text-align: left;"><br>
<br>
<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"><br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></h2>
<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Goal</span></h2>
Everyone loves Chef Bob's pizza and to make his business more efficent
he wants to create an online system for placing orders.&nbsp; He has
asked you to help him! To get the job done you will be using HTML and
JavaScript&nbsp; make a custom pizza order form for Chef Bob.&nbsp;
Create an order form that asks for the person's name,what size
pizza(small,medium or large) and what toppings they would like on their
pizza(such as peppperoni, extra cheese, etc.). All items should have
prices next to them. When the person is done ordering they should press
submit and get a total price. If a person forgets to fill out a field
they should get an error message telling them what they missed on the
form. Feel free to add pictures and graphics to make the form look
nice. <br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Concepts</h2>
After completing this lesson you should understand how to use:<br>
<ul>
  <li>Forms</li>
  <li>Checkboxes</li>
  <li>Radio Buttons</li>
  <li>Input Fields</li>
  <li>Submit Button</li>
  <li>Error Checking</li>
  <li>JavaScript</li>
</ul>
<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Steps</h2>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">1.Create the form using HTML</span><ol>
  
</ol>
<code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br>
&lt;html&gt;
<br>
&lt;head&gt;
<br>
&lt;title&gt;Your title&lt;/title&gt;
<br>
&lt;script&gt;
<br>
This is where the JavaScript goes<br>
&lt;/script&gt;
<br>
&lt;/head&gt;<br>
&lt;body&gt;
<br>
&lt;form&gt;
This is where all the input fields go(check boxes, radio buttons, etc.)
<br>
&lt;/form&gt;
<br>
&lt;img src="image.jpg&gt; how to add a picture<br>
&lt;/body&gt;
<br>
&lt;/html&gt;</code> <br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">2.This is an example of a checkbox</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>
&lt;input type="checkbox"&nbsp; value="sausage" name="top" /&gt; Sausage ($1.00) &lt;br /&gt;<br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">3.This is an example of a radio button</span><br>
<br>
&lt;input type="radio"&nbsp; value="small" name="size" /&gt; Small: $6.00<br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">4.This is an example of an input field</span><br>
<br>
First Name: &lt;input type="text" id="name" /&gt;<br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">5.Add JavaScript for error checking </span><br>
<br>
This example checks to make sure the name input is filled out<br>
<br>
function validateName()<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; var theName=
document.getElementById("name").value;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; if (theName.length == 0)<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; var error = "Name is missing.";<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return error;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; else<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
{&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; return ""<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">5.When submit is pressed give the total price</span><br>
<br>
<br>
<h2 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Want to make your form even better?</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Allow them to order more than one pizza</li>
  <li>Show a picture of the pizza that they ordered</li>
  <li>Link it to an actual online pizza place</li>
  <li>Add garlic knots, salads and drinks</li>
  <li>Calculate tip and tax for the order</li>
  <li>Try using another language like Scratch or Java<br>
    <br>
  </li>
</ul>
